<p>Anyone is welcome to attend our lab meetings, which are currently being held virtually. See the <a href="http://roboticexplorationlab.org/calendar.html">lab calendar</a> for details.</p>

<h3 id="prospective-graduate-students">Prospective Graduate Students</h3>
<p>If you are interested in working in our lab, please apply to one of the <a href="https://www.ri.cmu.edu/ri-education/">graduate programs offered by the Robotics Institute</a>. Please contact Zac after you have been admitted.</p>

<h3 id="carnegie-mellon-graduate-students">Carnegie Mellon Graduate Students</h3>
<p>If you have been admitted to CMU and are interested in joining our lab, send Zac an <a href="mailto:zacm@cmu.edu">email</a> with your CV and a short description of your background and interests. Also, feel free to join us for a group meeting at any time.</p>

<h3 id="carnegie-mellon-undergraduate-students">Carnegie Mellon Undergraduate Students</h3>
<p>We often have opportunities for undergraduates to get involved in our research. If youâ€™re interested in robots, spacecraft, or control systems, send Zac an <a href="mailto:zacm@cmu.edu">email</a> or join us for a group meeting.</p>

<h3 id="visiting-student-researchers">Visiting Student Researchers</h3>
